04:26.840 --> 04:28.842
There you are.

04:30.680 --> 04:31.841
What the--

04:34.840 --> 04:36.365
How'd you get in there?

04:40.080 --> 04:44.404
( Rock music playing )

04:50.200 --> 04:52.328
Hey, what's the ink?

04:52.520 --> 04:54.568
Woman:
It's from a French poem.

04:54.720 --> 04:56.722
Do you know any poetry?

04:56.880 --> 04:58.006
Mmm.

04:58.160 --> 05:01.642
That shit drives me wild.

05:01.800 --> 05:03.404
Well...

05:05.040 --> 05:07.725
it ain't French, but, uh...

05:10.240 --> 05:12.083
I got a little something for you.

05:13.720 --> 05:17.042
Check this out.
Come here.

05:17.200 --> 05:19.806
Look at that shit.

05:20.000 --> 05:22.241
- Yeah.
- That is fucking dope shit.

05:22.400 --> 05:26.291
It's inked in blood.
Here we go.

05:26.440 --> 05:29.205
Try this piece of poetry.
It'll blow your mind.

05:29.360 --> 05:31.408
Kunda...

05:32.760 --> 05:34.922
Tranya...

05:35.080 --> 05:37.606
Verata.

05:37.760 --> 05:40.240
Ash:
Mesartra.

05:40.440 --> 05:42.920
Mesartra!

05:43.080 --> 05:45.082
Mistropene.

05:45.280 --> 05:49.171
Mistropene!

05:49.320 --> 05:51.163
(laughing)

05:54.920 --> 05:58.129
( laughter and music fades )

05:58.280 --> 05:59.611
Fuck.

05:59.760 --> 06:02.764
( Theme music playing )

06:06.280 --> 06:10.285
(whooshing )

06:28.000 --> 06:31.322
(wind chimes tinkling)

06:42.600 --> 06:43.647
Man:
Neighbors report a woman

06:43.840 --> 06:45.490
- screaming for her life.
- ( cocks shotgun )

06:45.640 --> 06:48.371
I was kind of expecting
a shit show.

06:48.520 --> 06:51.171
Yeah, quiet's not good, either.

06:51.320 --> 06:55.041
- ( Ghostly shriek)
- What's that?

06:56.880 --> 06:58.166
You take the front.

07:17.840 --> 07:19.444
State police.

07:19.600 --> 07:21.250
Anyone here?

07:21.400 --> 07:24.324
( Door creaks open )

07:49.640 --> 07:51.608
( panting )

07:52.720 --> 07:55.200
- Carson.
- ( static hissing )

07:57.240 --> 07:58.844
- John.
- ( static hissing )

08:00.240 --> 08:01.571
( creaking )

08:03.080 --> 08:07.404
( creaking continues )

08:13.520 --> 08:14.601
( gasps )

08:14.800 --> 08:17.406
( creaking )

08:27.440 --> 08:29.647
Something's not right here.

08:29.800 --> 08:31.370
(woman whimpering )

08:31.520 --> 08:35.081
(whimpering continues )

08:42.760 --> 08:45.240
John:
Oh, my God.

08:45.400 --> 08:47.448
(whimpering continues )

08:51.960 --> 08:53.928
Ma'am?

09:02.600 --> 09:07.128
(whimpering )

09:23.160 --> 09:25.845
State police, ma'am.

09:26.040 --> 09:27.530
I'm going to need you
to put your hands up.

09:27.680 --> 09:29.489
You need to do
what he says, lady.

09:29.640 --> 09:32.644
Hands up.
Nice and slow.

09:37.000 --> 09:41.005
( Ghostly whispering )

09:41.160 --> 09:44.050
( speaking foreign language )

09:44.200 --> 09:45.361
What did she say?

09:45.560 --> 09:47.881
I said...

09:48.040 --> 09:49.405
burn in hell!

09:58.600 --> 10:01.046
( Shrieking )

10:04.600 --> 10:07.843
We know who you are!

10:29.440 --> 10:31.204
( Shrieks )

10:38.760 --> 10:41.969
(growling )

10:48.400 --> 10:51.722
What the hell was that?

10:53.560 --> 10:55.927
- (shrieks )
- Aah!

11:02.280 --> 11:06.808
I'm going to cut you up
into little pieces!

11:10.080 --> 11:14.608
( Banging )

11:29.760 --> 11:31.000
Carson!

11:33.720 --> 11:35.609
<i>_</i> ( skittering )
" Oh!

11:37.400 --> 11:40.483
- ( Skittering )
- ( clanking )

11:45.680 --> 11:47.011
Ah!

11:56.960 --> 11:59.566
- ( Screams )
- ( growling )

12:07.800 --> 12:10.201
( <i>shouts</i> )

12:10.360 --> 12:11.691
Aah!

12:16.200 --> 12:17.326
( Shrieks )

12:17.480 --> 12:20.404
(moaning )

12:20.560 --> 12:22.164
Don't.

12:25.480 --> 12:26.845
Don't shoot me.

12:28.320 --> 12:30.209
Please, Amanda.

12:33.920 --> 12:36.241
I'm your friend.

12:41.160 --> 12:42.685
I need you.

12:45.200 --> 12:47.362
You need me?

12:49.000 --> 12:50.365
I need you...

12:51.520 --> 12:52.521
to die.

13:01.520 --> 13:04.490
(laughing)

13:17.360 --> 13:19.681
( roars )

13:21.640 --> 13:23.449
Aah!

13:23.600 --> 13:26.444
( Birds chirping )

13:37.760 --> 13:39.569
(dialing )

13:42.440 --> 13:43.441
Yeah, hi.

13:43.600 --> 13:45.762
I came in there many years ago

13:45.920 --> 13:49.641
and we chatted about
a particular book.

13:49.800 --> 13:50.801
It was, uh,

13:50.960 --> 13:52.610
bound in human flesh,
inked in blood.

13:52.760 --> 13:56.606
Anyway, I might need
some help translating that.

13:56.760 --> 13:58.922
Oh. Okay, great.

13:59.080 --> 14:00.923
Yeah, I'll see you soon.
Thank you.

14:01.080 --> 14:02.081
( Beeps )

14:02.240 --> 14:03.605
Morning, Vivian!

14:03.760 --> 14:06.001
Hey, I wonder if I can ask you
a teeny favor.

14:06.160 --> 14:07.764
Some things have come up

14:07.920 --> 14:10.048
and, well, I may have to
leave town soon.

14:10.240 --> 14:12.891
Oh, honey-pie,
that's a shame.

14:13.080 --> 14:15.765
Any chance you could tidy up
my trailer while I'm gone?

14:15.920 --> 14:17.365
No heavy lifting, of course.

14:17.520 --> 14:19.249
Just a little dusting,
some dishes,

14:19.400 --> 14:21.164
oil up the hitch,
make sure it's ready to go,

14:21.320 --> 14:22.321
and drain the wastewater tank?

14:22.480 --> 14:26.690
Uh, anything for you,
you sweet little muffin.

14:26.880 --> 14:28.803
Really get in there, okay?

14:28.960 --> 14:31.122
Conquer those clogs.

14:31.280 --> 14:32.964
Thank you,
my delicious cookie.

14:38.640 --> 14:40.290
Woman's voice:
Ash.

14:43.480 --> 14:45.323
Ash.

14:48.840 --> 14:52.162
Ash.

15:19.280 --> 15:21.567
Aah!

15:21.720 --> 15:23.529
We are near.

15:25.160 --> 15:28.642
Your time comes again.

15:40.200 --> 15:41.361
Watch out, you idiot!

15:41.520 --> 15:43.204
Ah, shut up.

15:50.520 --> 15:53.808
Okay, I'll just get my check,

15:53.960 --> 15:56.088
and I'll be in Saginaw
before nightfall.

15:56.240 --> 15:57.890
( Muzak playing )

15:58.040 --> 16:00.850
Hey, Mr. Roper.

16:01.000 --> 16:02.365
My dear friend Eli is sick,

16:02.560 --> 16:05.211
so I got to take off early,
you know, to look after him.

16:05.400 --> 16:07.050
Anyway I can pick up my check
before I go?

16:07.200 --> 16:08.884
Are you really going to use
your fucking lizard

16:09.040 --> 16:11.088
as an excuse
to get out of work again?

16:11.280 --> 16:14.284
- I am.
- Okay.

16:14.440 --> 16:16.727
Look, you retard--

16:16.880 --> 16:18.086
and I can say "retard"

16:18.240 --> 16:20.720
because my gardener
is a huge one--

16:20.880 --> 16:22.723
I know all about you.

16:22.880 --> 16:25.360
You think you can't get fired
because you have seniority?

16:25.520 --> 16:27.409
Well...

16:27.560 --> 16:28.721
okay, technically, you're correct,

16:28.920 --> 16:30.888
but that doesn't mean
I have to help you.

16:31.040 --> 16:33.771
Soto be clear,
that's a nay-no on the paycheck?

16:33.920 --> 16:35.410
You get your pay
at the end of the day.

16:35.560 --> 16:36.800
That's store policy.

16:36.960 --> 16:39.201
Now take these
light bulbs out back

16:39.360 --> 16:40.566
and don't break them.

16:40.720 --> 16:42.927
Okay, Mr. Roper.
Right away, sir.

16:44.760 --> 16:45.921
( Clattering )

16:50.920 --> 16:51.921
Shh.

16:53.080 --> 16:54.923
( P°Pping )

17:10.119 --> 17:12.805
- I got this.
- Aw, thanks, Pablo.

17:12.960 --> 17:13.961
Oh, great news.

17:14.119 --> 17:15.609
I got some turkey burgers.

17:15.800 --> 17:16.961
You know, we can grill
and watch a little

17:17.119 --> 17:18.406
"Monday Night Raw" tonight
if you want.

17:18.560 --> 17:20.961
Aw, tonight's bad.

17:21.119 --> 17:22.804
I mean, actually,
I just came in to get my check

17:22.960 --> 17:25.486
because I may have to skip town.

17:25.640 --> 17:27.801
What?
No, you can't leave.

17:27.960 --> 17:29.325
You're, like, the coolest thing
about this place.

17:29.520 --> 17:30.521
That's very true,

17:30.680 --> 17:34.810
but I may have
a, uh, situation.

17:36.480 --> 17:37.481
Hey, man,
tell me what's up.

17:37.640 --> 17:38.641
Maybe I can help you.

17:38.800 --> 17:40.165
I wish I could,
but with all due respect,

17:40.320 --> 17:43.210
your tiny brain is a lot safer
with my problems inside it.

17:43.360 --> 17:45.328
Hey, man, I seen a lot
between Honduras and here.

17:45.480 --> 17:47.448
- Try me.
- Honduras?

17:47.600 --> 17:48.601
You said you were from New Jersey.

17:48.760 --> 17:51.331
Oh, did I?
I am-- was from there.

17:51.480 --> 17:52.527
Anyway, hey, look,
it's a terrible thing

17:52.680 --> 17:53.681
that you're leaving right now

17:53.880 --> 17:56.008
because I just got
my upstairs neighbor hired.

17:56.160 --> 17:58.686
That's one more person
to look out for you, you know,

17:58.840 --> 18:01.161
like, when you take your naps
or you come in late

18:01.320 --> 18:02.367
or don't come in at all.

18:02.520 --> 18:05.171
Well, I do love
a partner in crime.

18:05.320 --> 18:07.527
Where is he?

18:07.680 --> 18:09.330
Right there.

18:09.520 --> 18:11.170
Right there. Aisle three.

18:11.360 --> 18:13.681
Ash:
Sweet musical Jesus!

18:13.840 --> 18:15.604
That's your friend?

18:15.760 --> 18:19.685
Aw, she's filthy--
and fine.

18:19.840 --> 18:21.604
She's very attractive, I know.

18:21.760 --> 18:23.888
Hey, I try not
to look at her like that.

18:24.080 --> 18:25.844
- That must be difficult.
- It is.

18:26.040 --> 18:29.203
She haunts my dreams.
Just kidding.

18:29.360 --> 18:30.521
She does, though.

18:30.680 --> 18:32.364
Well, I should say my good-byes.

18:32.520 --> 18:34.249
( Light bulbs popping )

18:40.040 --> 18:42.361
Nice day, huh?

18:42.520 --> 18:45.683
Just wanted to say I'm sorry
I have to leave you so soon.

18:45.840 --> 18:47.888
I don't even know you.

18:48.040 --> 18:50.611
And now you never will...

18:50.760 --> 18:52.046
which is fine,

18:52.200 --> 18:54.567
because you really never
could have had me anyway.

18:55.560 --> 18:57.403
Had you?

18:57.560 --> 18:58.607
Are you out of your mind?

18:58.760 --> 19:00.285
( laughs )
I know.

19:00.440 --> 19:02.408
It sounds crazy, doesn't it?

19:02.560 --> 19:04.847
I'm old, graying,
10 pounds overweight.

19:05.000 --> 19:06.729
- 10?
- Okay, 30 pounds overweight,

19:06.880 --> 19:08.086
but It doesn't matter.

19:08.240 --> 19:09.401
At some point,

19:09.560 --> 19:12.609
the thought would have
occurred to you.

19:12.760 --> 19:15.730
Do me a favor, will you?
Thank your mother for me.

19:15.920 --> 19:19.367
She passed her genes down to you
in all the right places.

19:20.560 --> 19:24.610
My mother died in a car accident
six months ago.

19:27.400 --> 19:30.927
Wow. Phew.

19:31.080 --> 19:32.445
Um, you know, in the future,

19:32.600 --> 19:35.604
you might want to just say
"Sure, I'll tell her."

19:35.760 --> 19:37.603
Because a bomb like that
on somebody you just met

19:37.760 --> 19:38.761
is downright rude.

19:38.920 --> 19:41.844
But you know what?
You're young.

19:42.000 --> 19:43.161
You'll figure it out.

19:45.000 --> 19:46.604
Good-bye forever, Kelly.

19:50.120 --> 19:51.201
Touch me again,

19:51.360 --> 19:52.771
and you're going to need
another wooden hand.

19:52.960 --> 19:53.961
Okay, wait.

19:54.120 --> 19:55.963
Another wooden hand
in place of my real hand?

19:56.120 --> 19:57.610
Or another wooden hand
in place of my wooden hand?

19:57.760 --> 19:59.842
- Your real hand!
- ( grunts )

20:00.000 --> 20:01.604
( groans )

20:04.960 --> 20:06.450
Touchy.

20:12.280 --> 20:14.681
( Door chime tinkles )

20:14.840 --> 20:17.161
( police radio chatter)

20:17.360 --> 20:18.646
Morning, GUYS-

20:18.800 --> 20:19.801
- Hey.
- Good morning.

20:19.960 --> 20:21.803
( Police radio chatter continues )

20:21.960 --> 20:23.325
- Coffee?
- Yeah.

20:23.480 --> 20:25.164
Sure.

20:25.320 --> 20:26.845
( Chattering )

20:27.000 --> 20:30.322
(whispering )

20:34.800 --> 20:37.167
Amanda.

20:37.320 --> 20:39.800
I can't imagine
what you're going through,

20:39.960 --> 20:42.327
but you'll be back to work
before you know it.

20:42.480 --> 20:44.847
Yeah, maybe,

20:45.000 --> 20:49.847
if I can clear and Internal Affairs
homicide inquest,

20:50.000 --> 20:52.731
plus or minus a psych evaluation.

20:52.880 --> 20:55.087
( Sighs )

20:55.240 --> 20:59.290
I don't know.

21:04.000 --> 21:07.368
( Ghostly rumble )

21:11.400 --> 21:12.561
( gasps )

21:19.240 --> 21:21.891
(whispering )

21:26.520 --> 21:27.885
Are you all right?

21:29.200 --> 21:30.725
Yeah, I, um--

21:30.880 --> 21:34.566
I just--
just thought I saw something.

21:34.720 --> 21:38.406
But I can't really trust
my eyes these days.

21:38.560 --> 21:40.164
There's nothing wrong
with your eyes.

21:40.360 --> 21:42.203
Sometimes
what you think you saw

21:42.400 --> 21:44.767
is exactly what you saw.

21:48.440 --> 21:49.965
( Bell on door rings )

21:57.520 --> 21:58.726
( clattering )

21:58.920 --> 22:00.081
Mr. Roper:
Hey, William!

22:00.240 --> 22:02.083
Bing those bulbs back here!

22:02.240 --> 22:04.402
( Squeaky voice )
Okay, Mr. Roper!

22:09.760 --> 22:13.367
Hey! Man working here!
Lights on!

22:13.560 --> 22:15.244
( Giggle echoes )

22:16.240 --> 22:17.401
Who's there?

22:20.760 --> 22:22.922
( Giggle echoes )

22:27.760 --> 22:29.285
Who's there?

22:48.600 --> 22:50.602
Hmm.

22:59.800 --> 23:01.131
